Increament & Decreament Operator:->


Expression		initial value of x			value of y			final value of x
y=++x			10							11					11
y=x++			10							10					11
y=--x			10							9					9
y=x--			10							10					9

Loop Hole:->
=======================================================================================================================
-> we can apply increament and decreament operators only for variables but not for constant values.if we are trying 
to apply for constant values then we will get compile time error.


int x = 10;
int y = ++x;
sysout(x);

output:
11

int x = 10;
int y = ++10;
syosut(x);

output:
CE: unexpected type found value required variable.
========================================================================================================================
-> nesting of increament and decreament operators not allowed.

int x = 10;
int y = ++(++x);
sysout(10);

output:
CE:unexpected type required variable found value.
========================================================================================================================
-> for final variables we can't apply increament and decreament operators.
int x = 10;
x =11;
sysout(x);

output:
11

final int x = 10;
x++;
syosut(x);

output:
CE:can't assign a value to final variable x
========================================================================================================================
-> we can apply increament and decreament operators for every primitive type except boolean.

int x = 10;
x++;
sysout(x);

output:
11

char ch ='a';
ch++;
sysout(ch);

output:
b

double d = 10.5;
d++;
sysout(d);

output:
11.5

boolean b = true;
b++;
sysout(b);

output:
CE:operator ++ can't applied to boolean
=======================================================================================================================
-> difference between b++ and b = b+1 

byte b = 10;
b = b+1;
sysout(b);

output:
CE

byte b = 10;
b++;
sysout(b);

output:
11

byte a = 10;
byte b = 20;
byte c = a+b;
sysout(c);

output:->
CE:possible loss of precision found byte required int.




























